    </selectionEntry>
    <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="Neutron Bomb" hidden="false" id="a74f-010a-42ac-9d13">
      <costs>
        <cost name="Point(s)" typeId="9893-c379-920b-8982" value="0"/>
        <cost name="Reaction Point(s)" typeId="c9ba-097e-c47f-ecc2" value="0"/>
        <cost name="Auxiliary Detachment(s)" typeId="3e8e-05ee-be52-12d6" value="0"/>
        <cost name="Apex Detachment(s)" typeId="159d-855c-533d-f592" value="0"/>
        <cost name="Combined Warlord and Lord of War Points" typeId="14bd-cad0-cd3d-8b23" value="0"/>
        <cost name="Mech LB" typeId="7275-cbe8-a563-7152" value="0"/>
        <cost name="Asset Point(s)" typeId="29b4-fb27-da17-1e21" value="1"/>
      </costs>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink targetId="b720-ea51-7339-6a08" id="1a65-e6ba-025e-3161" primary="true" name="Asset"/>
      </categoryLinks>
      <profiles>
        <profile name="Neutron Bomb" typeId="7ae0-de68-04c6-8d8f" typeName="Asset" hidden="false" id="b616-d64c-7dc9-e233">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Summary" typeId="3dcf-9034-fc2d-cd56">When triggered, Vehicle and Walker Models near a Neutron Bomb may gain the Suppressed Tactical Status.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Setup" typeId="e965-60bc-cd79-63e7">Each Neutron Bomb Marker must be set up by the Player that selected it at the end of the Prepare the Battlefield Step of the Mission Sequence.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Effect" typeId="bbd3-5482-ed3a-a3b3">If a Unit is selected to move in the Movement Phase or make a Charge Move while any Models from that Unit with the Vehicle or Walker Type are within 6&quot; of the centre of a Neutron Bomb Marker, the Controlling Player of that Unit must roll one Dice for each Model from that Unit which is within 6&quot; of the centre of a Neutron Bomb Marker. On a 4+, that Model triggers the Neutron Bomb and the Unit that includes that Model gains the Suppressed Tactical Status, and that Neutron Bomb Marker is removed from the Battlefield.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="How To Destroy" typeId="6888-e488-df3f-edcf">Removed when triggered (see above).</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Traits" typeId="a1e3-4f30-fa22-d127">Defender, Minefield</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <modifiers>
        <modifier type="set" value="true" field="hidden">
          <conditions>
            <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="roster" childId="affa-726d-7fee-f272" shared="true" childName="Attacker" includeChildSelections="true" includeChildForces="true"/>
          </conditions>
          <comment>Hidden From Attackers</comment>
        </modifier>
      </modifiers>
    </selectionEntry>
    <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="Auto-Repair Servitor Clade" hidden="false" id="2f1a-ca50-8f54-abfb">
      <costs>
        <cost name="Point(s)" typeId="9893-c379-920b-8982" value="0"/>
        <cost name="Reaction Point(s)" typeId="c9ba-097e-c47f-ecc2" value="0"/>
        <cost name="Auxiliary Detachment(s)" typeId="3e8e-05ee-be52-12d6" value="0"/>
        <cost name="Apex Detachment(s)" typeId="159d-855c-533d-f592" value="0"/>
        <cost name="Combined Warlord and Lord of War Points" typeId="14bd-cad0-cd3d-8b23" value="0"/>
        <cost name="Mech LB" typeId="7275-cbe8-a563-7152" value="0"/>
        <cost name="Asset Point(s)" typeId="29b4-fb27-da17-1e21" value="2"/>
      </costs>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink targetId="b720-ea51-7339-6a08" id="acf4-e204-704c-120e" primary="true" name="Asset"/>
      </categoryLinks>
      <profiles>
        <profile name="Auto-Repair Servitor Clade" typeId="7ae0-de68-04c6-8d8f" typeName="Asset" hidden="false" id="785c-4a10-c618-056e">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Summary" typeId="3dcf-9034-fc2d-cd56">Auto-Repair Servitor Clades can assist in removing Tactical Statuses from friendly Vehicle Models.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Setup" typeId="e965-60bc-cd79-63e7">Each Auto-Repair Servitor Clade Marker is set up by the Player that selected it at the start of the Deploy Armies Step. It must be set up with the centre of the Marker anywhere within that Player&apos;s Deployment Zone.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Effect" typeId="bbd3-5482-ed3a-a3b3">At the start of the Defender&apos;s Statuses Sub-Phase, that Player can select one Model with the Vehicle Type that is within 4&quot; of the centre of the Auto-Repair Servitor Clade Marker they set up. Until the end of that Sub-Phase, that Vehicle has the Auto-Repair (4+) Special Rule.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="How To Destroy" typeId="6888-e488-df3f-edcf">If a Blast Marker covers the centre of an Auto-Repair Servitor Clade Marker, then after that Shooting Attack has been resolved, the Controlling Player of the Unit making the Shooting Attack must roll one Dice. On a 4+, that Auto-Repair Servitor Clade Marker is removed.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Traits" typeId="a1e3-4f30-fa22-d127">Defender</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <modifiers>
        <modifier type="set" value="true" field="hidden">
          <conditions>
            <condition type="atLeast" value="1" field="selections" scope="roster" childId="affa-726d-7fee-f272" shared="true" childName="Attacker" includeChildSelections="true" includeChildForces="true"/>
          </conditions>
          <comment>Hidden From Attackers</comment>
        </modifier>
      </modifiers>
      <infoLinks>
        <infoLink name="Auto-Repair (X)" id="5477-baa8-6883-0a9a" hidden="false" type="rule" targetId="3973-ed50-1482-ff4a">
          <modifiers>
            <modifier type="set" value="Auto-Repair (4+)" field="name"/>
          </modifiers>
          <comment>4+</comment>
        </infoLink>
      </infoLinks>
    </selectionEntry>
    <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="Wayfinder Device" hidden="false" id="897a-1ca7-ce3c-c361">
      <costs>
        <cost name="Point(s)" typeId="9893-c379-920b-8982" value="0"/>
        <cost name="Reaction Point(s)" typeId="c9ba-097e-c47f-ecc2" value="0"/>
